    "created_at": "2015-09-23T08:55:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-23T08:55:16Z",
    "body": "A blank window of Electron opens 36 unix socket files on my machine, while a blink window of chromium-browser opens 44 files.\n\nI think the answer is Chromium's multiple process architecture, an instance of Electron has at least 3 processes open, if the crash-reporter is used then there is 4, and they have to communicate with each other with IPC. Also the main process opens about 30 threads for various things like doing IO and watching networking configs, some of them may have a pool of handles for caching.\n\nAtom take a few more handles because it needs to watch your project's root for filesystem events, plus a few workers doing syntax highlighting, spell checking, etc.\n\nSo adding all of them up I think 36 is a reasonable number for Electron, and 56 is not that bad for Atom. And since Electron opens the same level of numbers of handles with Chromium, I think this is expected. You can probably go to http://crbug.com to report this to Chromium's issues tracker.\n"
  },
