    "created_at": "2015-09-23T19:15:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-23T19:15:57Z",
    "body": "@paulcbetts is right. when I hit the maximum number, it stops me from creating any new windows at all--for anything. I get this repeated over and over again in my .xsession-errors until I close out a few things:\n\n```\nMaximum number of clients reached\nCan't open display.\n```\n\nI can see why this could be seen as a reasonable number. The question of whose bug it is may be reasonable, @zcbenz, this has been reported to Chromium's issue tracker a few times.\n\nHowever, Chromium seems to keep the number of sockets they have open under a bit better control than either Atom or Slack--I've seen Atom get a lot higher than 57. And, when I hit that max number, Chromium doesn't have a problem closing. Electron processes don't always close gracefully when that happens, which is why I'm not sure this is a purely Chromium problem.\n\nBut, again, I don't really know the internals all that well, so I could be wrong.\n"
  },
