    "created_at": "2015-09-28T06:00:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-28T06:34:22Z",
    "body": "I've also been bitten by this bug - also in the Slack app. It seems to be leaking Xorg connections over time. I suspect the opening and closing the app through the tray icon is doing this, but it was rather inconsistent. In addition every desktop notification leaks one Xorg connection - this one is every time. \n\nYou can monitor the Xorg connections through:\n\n```\nlsof -p [Xorg PID] | grep /tmp/.X11-unix/X0 | wc -l\n```\n\nxrestop reports the new connections as unknown, for instance:\n\n```\n79 - <unknown> ( PID:  ?   ):\nres_base      : ox400000\nres_mask      : ox1fffff\nwindows       : 0\nGCs           : 0\nfonts         : 0\npixmaps       : 0\npictures      : 0\nglyphsets     : 0\ncolormaps     : 0\npassive grabs : 0\ncursors       : 0\nunknowns      : 0\npixmap bytes  : 0\nother bytes   : ~0\ntotal bytes   : ~0\n```\n\nClosing the app frees them, but not before that.\n"
  },
